
GadTools Attribute Tags
=======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GT_VisualInfo: ( ti_Tag = $80080034 )

Specify in ti_Data the result of the
GetVisualInfo call for GadTools.


GadTools Attribute Tags
=======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GT_Underscore: ( ti_Tag = $80080040 )

Specify in ti_Data a pointer to the
symbol that preceeds the character 
to be underlined in a gadget label.


GadTools Cycle Tags
===================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTCY_Labels: ( ti_Tag = $8008000E )

Specify in ti_Data a pointer to a
NULL pointer terminated array of
strings to use for the Cycle choices.


GadTools Cycle Tags
===================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTCY_Active: ( ti_Tag = $8008000F )

Specify an unsigned WORD in ti_Data,
counting from zero, to select the initial
active item.


GadTools Text Tags
==================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTTX_Text: ( ti_Tag = $8008000B )

Specify a pointer to a NULL terminated
string in ti_Data, to be used as the text
displayed in the gadget.


GadTools Text Tags
==================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTTX_CopyText: ( ti_Tag = $8008000C )

Specify a True boolean to have the gadget
take a copy the text instead of just
using the pointer to the string later.


GadTools Text Tags
==================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTTX_Border: ( ti_Tag = $80080039 )

Specify a True boolean to have the text
surrounded by a recessed border when drawn.


GadTools CheckBox Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTCB_Checked: ( ti_Tag = $80080004 )

Specify a True boolean to have the Gadget
selected (A tick present).


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTLV_Top: ( ti_Tag = $80080005 )

Specify in ti_Data the ordinal number of
the top item visible in the listview.


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTLV_Labels: ( ti_Tag = $80080006 )

Specify a List pointer in ti_data, to an 
Exec List whose nodes have their ln_Name
fields set to the items to be displayed
in the ListView.


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTLV_ReadOnly: ( ti_Tag = $80080007 )

Specify a boolean True in ti_Data 
to create a readonly ListView, in which 
items cannot be selected.


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTLV_ScrollWidth: ( ti_Tag = $80080008 )

Specify an Unsigned WORD in ti_Data
for the width of the scrollbar.


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTLV_ShowSelected: ( ti_Tag = $80080035 )

Specify a Gadget pointer in ti_Data as follows:

NULL: A read only TEXT_KIND display of the
      currently selected item.

Pointer to STRING_KIND: Allow the user to directly
      edit the current item.


GadTools ListView Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTLV_Selected: ( ti_Tag = $80080036 )

Specify the ordinal number of the item
to be selected initially in the current
selection display given by GTLV_ShowSelected.

Ignored if GTLV_ShowSelected is not used.


GadTools MutualExclude Tags
===========================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTMX_Labels: ( ti_Tag = $80080009 )

Specify in ti_Data a pointer to a
NULL pointer terminated array of
strings to use for the MX choice labels.


GadTools MutualExclude Tags
===========================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTMX_Active: ( ti_Tag = $80080010 )

Specify the ordinal number of the
selected item in ti_Data.


GadTools MutualExclude Tags
===========================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTMX_Spacing: ( ti_Tag = $8008003D )

Value specified in ti_Data is added to
font height to provide spacing between
MX choices.


GadTools Scroller Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSC_Top: ( ti_Tag = $80080015 )

Specify in ti_Data the top line or
position visible in the area that the
scroller represents.


GadTools Scroller Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSC_Total: ( ti_Tag = $80080016 )

Specify in ti_Data the total number of
lines or positions that the scroller
represents.


GadTools Scroller Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSC_Visible: ( ti_Tag = $80080017 )

Specify in ti_Data the number of
visible lines or positions for the 
scroller.


GadTools Scroller Tags
======================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSC_Arrows: ( ti_Tag = $8008003B )

Specifies that arrow gadgets are
attached to the scroller. The value in
ti_Data gives the width of the arrows for
a horizontal scroller, or the height for
a vertical scroller.

